Tips for Using SELECT DISTINCT:
- Use DISTINCT to remove duplicate rows from your result.
- DISTINCT applies to all selected columns together.
- Use DISTINCT with ORDER BY to sort unique values.
- Use COUNT(DISTINCT ...) to count unique values when supported by your database.
- In Access, use a subquery when COUNT(DISTINCT ...) is not supported.

Key Points:
- SELECT DISTINCT removes duplicate rows from the result.
- SELECT DISTINCT column1, column2 returns unique combinations.
- Use COUNT(DISTINCT column) to count unique values when supported.
- In Access, use a distinct subquery inside Count(*).

